                <note rend="inline" type="source">724.3415/1234: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Brazil</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Morgan</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Rio de Janeiro</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-06-24T16:00:00-03:00"
                            >June 24, 1931—4 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 4:03 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>39. Department’s telegram 41, June 23, 1 p.m. Communicated the substance of said
                    telegram to Foreign Minister today, will instruct Brazilian Ambassador,
                    Washington, to confer with you. Minister is prepared to support fully notes to
                    Bolivia and Paraguay referred to in telegram No. 41.</p>
                <p>Foreign Minister has learned that important Bolivian military officers are being
                    sent to Chaco and that one of them who had been assigned to assist in
                    demarcation of Brazilian-Bolivian frontier has been detailed to superintend
                    military operations in that region, also that Argentina has suggested that
                    Bolivia accept a military mission similar to the Argentine military mission in
                    Paraguay, but Chile objects on the score that such missions should not be
                    obtained from countries which are neighbors.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Morgan</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
